                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I personally mobs default programming is to go for enchanter (biggest threat) unless acted upon by an outside force like taunt. Ive seen this happen many, many times when killing the Pirate captains in Nek forest.
<br />

<br />
Guardian pulls group with bow. The mob hit hit with bow goes for the tank, the other 2 come at me like clockwork. I wasnt casting any spells. I wasnt out in front...they just come for me over and over. ITs part of the AI, think about it, if you are a group of 3 mobs, your best chance to win is to kill then enchanter fast and then hopefully hit the cleric before tank manages to get aggro. It can and does happen. 
<br />

<br />
My advice is: Learn to live with it because it only seems to get more noticable as you level up higher. I had a tank pull the Citadel with a bow while i stood way off to the side watching. Nothing like watching the tank die in a few hit from the one mob he hit with bow while 5-6 of his buddies are running at sow speed right for you!. Oh ya and they never give up chase    <img src="images/smiles/icon_axe.gif" alt="icon_axe.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
