                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">&lt;--- obviously now a squishy type <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I don't have any answers, but what I've seen is:
<br />

<br />
Me L18 (pre-Breeze) in a full group with cleric, druid, pred, 2 x tank. Fallen Gate, killing dragoons. I'm a good four-five levels lower than the others (they're all 22 thru 24).
<br />

<br />
Where we camping there's a pop right on us, and one across the way, as well as a few further out in the room.
<br />

<br />
Tank or predator always pull, unless there's a pop on our heads. Tank is a top taunter and everything sticks to him like glue - and I'm throwing dots and nukes about with total abandon, nothing so much as looks at me. I am maintaining a couple of lowbie buffs. No mob cares.
<br />

<br />
*ping* I get Breeze, and start casting it on folks. Now it doesn't seem to matter if I cast out of combat, or in, the mobs suddenly hate me... I'm Number One Tasty Treat on the menu and they jump on me immediately, given half a chance. When tank pulls with bow, he gets the one he shot at and the rest jump on me for a round or two. 
<br />

<br />
Just my experiences.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">Ilira [L65 Coercer] Cazic Thule[retired]
