                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I do and I don't.
<br />

<br />
As a druid, now Warden, I have noticed that when I cast thorns right before the tank pulls (meaning he is still in camp and in the process of doing his self buffs), every random once in a while, the mobs he pulls back - the one he tagged will stick on him and the others just straight b-line for me. I have no clue what it is, whether it's buff recognition or not, but that seems to be the only reason they would choose to ignore him and come for me.
<br />

<br />
Luckily the tank I speak of is my husband who plays a monk, and they get some terrific aggro-getters/holders, so even when they look at me like dinner, he is able to rectify the situation in the blink of an eye.
<br />

<br />
It seems like the AI required to just recognize buffs precast on pull would be amazing, which is why I am torn as to whether that is the case or not, but I can't think of anything else.
<br />

<br />
