                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If I have no maintained buffs, (i.e. no breeze, no haste, no group buffs, etc) and my group's puller runs into agro range of mobs, and then runs back to group... the mobs will still beat on him first, and then on whoever casts/heals/etc like you'd expect.
<br />

<br />
If, however, I'm maintaining 6 breeze spells, group haste, Gift, Signet, etc. and the puller does the same thing... every single mob will be all over me like flies on s... anyway, maintaining spells does generate agro, and so does casting them.
<br />

<br />
Easier way to deal with this, is to make sure that your puller pulls with an encounter-taunt, to agro every mob that he's pulling.  This wont always keep you save, but it will prevent mobs from taking you out first.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

<br />
