                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Easier way to deal with this, is to make sure that your puller pulls with an encounter-taunt, to agro every mob that he's pulling. This wont always keep you save, but it will prevent mobs from taking you out first.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
   I imagine your tank will grumble something akin to "you play your class, I'll play mine" to you if you suggest this.
<br />

<br />
   There are two problems with this scheme.  The first is that AE taunts are on very long recast timers (30 seconds).  With widespread spawns, this means that the tank runs the risk of not taunting the entire spawn and being unable to do so if he blows his AE taunt for pulling.  The second is that the tank will end up pulling any nearby encounters as well, due to the short range of this effect.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
